                </div><div type="commentary">
                
	       <p>Although not adjacent to any of the contributors lists (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr065200</ref>, <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr065210</ref> and <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr097170</ref>), 
	           this fragment, which could not be clearly interpreted by the first editors, belongs clearly to that group. Lacking precisions about the lett size, we cannot decide to which list this fragment belonged, the more so that, as 
	           pointed out by <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/></bibl>, the display of letters at each line seems also slightly different (this argument should be taken cautiously, as we have only a drawing and a vey small part of 
	           the document).</p>
	       <p>For a possible identification of the name at line A.6, see <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr096700</ref>, line 7: Iason son of Biandros might be the same man or a relative.</p>
